{
  "page": "Mysaria",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\"><img alt=\"Lys.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/fd/Lys.svg/50px-Lys.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/fd/Lys.svg/75px-Lys.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/fd/Lys.svg/100px-Lys.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Mysaria</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\"><img alt=\"Lys.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/fd/Lys.svg/50px-Lys.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/fd/Lys.svg/75px-Lys.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/fd/Lys.svg/100px-Lys.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Mysaria_by_Hylora.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Mysaria by Hylora.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/51/Mysaria_by_Hylora.png/350px-Mysaria_by_Hylora.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"457\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/51/Mysaria_by_Hylora.png/525px-Mysaria_by_Hylora.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/51/Mysaria_by_Hylora.png/700px-Mysaria_by_Hylora.png 2x\" /></a><div>Mysaria, by Hylora ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Aliases</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>Misery, the White Worm</li><li>Lady Misery<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li><li>Lady Mysaria<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Mistress_of_whisperers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mistress of whisperers\">Mistress of whisperers</a> <small>(unofficial)</small></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">Blacks</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lysene</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/130_AC\" title=\"130 AC\">130&#160;AC</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Lover</th><td>\nPrince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rogue_Prince\" title=\"The Rogue Prince\">The Rogue Prince</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Princess_and_the_Queen\" title=\"The Princess and the Queen\">The Princess and the Queen</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">Played by</span></th><td>\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sonoya_Mizuno\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Sonoya Mizuno\">Sonoya Mizuno</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">TV series</span></th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i>: <a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon_-_Season_1\" title=\"House of the Dragon - Season 1\">Season 1</a> | <a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon_-_Season_2\" title=\"House of the Dragon - Season 2\">2</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Mysaria</b>, also called <b>Lady Misery</b>, was a dancer from <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a> who became the <a href=\"/index.php/Paramour\" title=\"Paramour\">paramour</a> of Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a> and the unofficial <a href=\"/index.php/Mistress_of_whisperers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mistress of whisperers\">mistress of whisperers</a> to Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the television adaptation <i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i>, Mysaria is portrayed by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sonoya_Mizuno\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Sonoya Mizuno\">Sonoya Mizuno</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Paramour\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Paramour</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Dance_of_the_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Dance of the Dragons</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Legacy\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Legacy</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#House_of_the_Dragon\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>House of the Dragon</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">8</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance\">Appearance</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mysaria&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Mysaria had skin pale as milk. She was lithe and lissome in her youth, but age thickened her body.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Because of her appearance and reputation, Mysaria was dubbed <i>Misery, the White Worm</i> by enemies and rivals.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_viserys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_viserys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> She spoke in a manner foreign to <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>While serving as <a href=\"/index.php/Mistress_of_whisperers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mistress of whisperers\">mistress of whisperers</a>, Mysaria wore a hooded robe of black velvet lined with blood-red <a href=\"/index.php/Silk\" title=\"Silk\">silk</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mysaria&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Paramour\">Paramour</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mysaria&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Paramour\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>While a dancing girl in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>, Mysaria became the favored lover of Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Around <a href=\"/index.php/105_AC\" title=\"105 AC\">105&#160;AC</a>, Mysaria became pregnant with Daemon's child while living at <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a>. Daemon gave his paramour a <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_egg\" title=\"Dragon egg\">dragon egg</a> for the child, which angered King <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys I Targaryen\">Viserys I Targaryen</a>. The king ordered Daemon to return the egg and send Mysaria back to <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a>. During her return to the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_City\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Free City\">Free City</a>, she lost the child during a storm on the <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_sea\" title=\"Narrow sea\">narrow sea</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Dance_of_the_Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mysaria&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Dance of the Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Mysaria_by_Warp_Speed.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/4b/Mysaria_by_Warp_Speed.png/350px-Mysaria_by_Warp_Speed.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"437\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/4b/Mysaria_by_Warp_Speed.png/525px-Mysaria_by_Warp_Speed.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/4/4b/Mysaria_by_Warp_Speed.png/700px-Mysaria_by_Warp_Speed.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Mysaria_by_Warp_Speed.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Mysaria, by Warp Speed ©</div></div></div>\n<p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a> desired revenge for the death of his stepson, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Lucerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Lucerys Velaryon\">Lucerys Velaryon</a>. With a pale stranger used as a go-between, two assassins, <a href=\"/index.php/Blood_(the_butcher)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Blood (the butcher)\">Blood</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Cheese_(the_rat-catcher)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Cheese (the rat-catcher)\">Cheese</a>, infiltrated the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a> and killed Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_Targaryen_(son_of_Aegon_II)\" title=\"Jaehaerys Targaryen (son of Aegon II)\">Jaehaerys Targaryen</a>, the eldest son of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a>. Blood was seized by the <a href=\"/index.php/Gold_cloaks\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gold cloaks\">gold cloaks</a> trying to leave the city, and he admitted under <a href=\"/index.php/Torture\" title=\"Torture\">torture</a> that he had been hired by a <a href=\"/index.php/Prostitute\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Prostitute\">prostitute</a>, a pale older woman, called Misery by the other harlots. However, the <a href=\"/index.php/Gold_cloaks\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gold cloaks\">gold cloaks</a> were unable to find Mysaria or Cheese.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Mysaria became Daemon's <a href=\"/index.php/Mistress_of_whisperers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mistress of whisperers\">mistress of whisperers</a> at some point.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_viserys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_viserys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> After the <a href=\"/index.php/Fall_of_King%27s_Landing\" title=\"Fall of King&#39;s Landing\">fall of King's Landing</a> to Rhaenyra, Mysaria served as the queen's mistress of whisperers in all but name, although she did not join the <a href=\"/index.php/Small_council\" title=\"Small council\">small council</a>. Rhaenyra apparently approved of Daemon sleeping with Mysaria each night.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>When Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Alicent_Hightower\" title=\"Alicent Hightower\">Alicent Hightower</a> referred to the deaths of Rhaenyra's sons by saying only <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastard</a> blood had been spilled, Rhaenyra was enraged, and threatened to <a href=\"/index.php/Tongue_mutilation\" title=\"Tongue mutilation\">cut out her tongue</a>. According to the <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Testimony_of_Mushroom\" title=\"The Testimony of Mushroom\">Testimony</a></i> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Fool\" title=\"Fool\">fool</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Mushroom\" title=\"Mushroom\">Mushroom</a>, Mysaria suggested a crueler punishment, proposing that the Dowager Queen and Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Helaena_Targaryen\" title=\"Helaena Targaryen\">Helaena Targaryen</a> be taken to a certain <a href=\"/index.php/Brothel_Queens\" title=\"Brothel Queens\">brothel</a> so they would be forcibly impregnated with bastard offspring. Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a> discounts Mushroom's story, however.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Following the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Battle_of_Tumbleton\" title=\"First Battle of Tumbleton\">First Battle of Tumbleton</a>, Mysaria informed Rhaenyra that Daemon had been sleeping with <a href=\"/index.php/Nettles\" title=\"Nettles\">Nettles</a>, his fellow <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonrider\" title=\"Dragonrider\">dragonrider</a>, at <a href=\"/index.php/Maidenpool\" title=\"Maidenpool\">Maidenpool</a>. Rhaenyra ordered the death of Nettles, but Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Manfryd_Mooton\" title=\"Manfryd Mooton\">Manfryd Mooton</a> disobeyed the command. Nettles disappeared on <a href=\"/index.php/Sheepstealer\" title=\"Sheepstealer\">Sheepstealer</a>, while Daemon flew on <a href=\"/index.php/Caraxes\" title=\"Caraxes\">Caraxes</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a> to await a <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_Above_the_Gods_Eye\" title=\"Battle Above the Gods Eye\">confrontation with his nephew</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>After Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a> was imprisoned for warning Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Addam_Velaryon\" title=\"Addam Velaryon\">Addam Velaryon</a> of his impending arrest under charges of treason, two of the Sea Snake's <a href=\"/index.php/Sworn_swords\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sworn swords\">sworn swords</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Denys_Woodwright\" title=\"Denys Woodwright\">Denys Woodwright</a> and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Thoron_True\" title=\"Thoron True\">Thoron True</a>, planned to free their <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lord</a>. Mysaria learned of the plan from a <a href=\"/index.php/Whore\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Whore\">whore</a> Thoron had been <a href=\"/index.php/Bedding\" title=\"Bedding\">bedding</a>, however, and the two <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knights</a> were promptly arrested and hanged. Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_(Dance_of_the_Dragons)\" title=\"Eustace (Dance of the Dragons)\">Eustace</a> suggests that Helaena Targaryen jumped to her death after being informed by Mysaria of how her son, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Maelor_Targaryen\" title=\"Maelor Targaryen\">Maelor Targaryen</a>, had been killed at <a href=\"/index.php/Sack_of_Bitterbridge\" title=\"Sack of Bitterbridge\">Bitterbridge</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Riot_of_King%27s_Landing_(Dance_of_the_Dragons)\" title=\"Riot of King&#39;s Landing (Dance of the Dragons)\">riot of King's Landing</a>, Mysaria warned Rhaenyra against the coming dark. When Rhaenyra ultimately <a href=\"/index.php/Flight_to_Dragonstone\" title=\"Flight to Dragonstone\">fled the capital</a>, Mysaria remained at the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a> among other members of the court. Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Garth_the_Harelip\" title=\"Garth the Harelip\">Garth the Harelip</a> surrendered the Red Keep to Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Perkin_the_Flea\" title=\"Perkin the Flea\">Perkin the Flea</a> and his <a href=\"/index.php/Gutter_knights\" title=\"Gutter knights\">gutter knights</a>, and Mysaria attempted to flee, but was taken. Perkin informed Mysaria that if she could <a href=\"/index.php/Walk_of_atonement\" title=\"Walk of atonement\">travel naked</a> through the city to the <a href=\"/index.php/Gate_of_the_Gods\" title=\"Gate of the Gods\">Gate of the Gods</a> while being whipped, she would be allowed to live. Mysaria only made it halfway, dying on the city's cobblestones.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Legacy\">Legacy</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mysaria&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Legacy\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Brynden_Rivers\" title=\"Brynden Rivers\">Brynden Rivers</a> was said to have rivaled Lady Misery as a <a href=\"/index.php/Master_of_whisperers\" title=\"Master of whisperers\">master of whisperers</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Mysaria_TV.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/c8/Mysaria_TV.jpg/350px-Mysaria_TV.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"515\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/c8/Mysaria_TV.jpg/525px-Mysaria_TV.jpg 1.5x, /images/c/c8/Mysaria_TV.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Mysaria_TV.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Sonoya Mizuno as Mysaria in <i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i></div></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"House_of_the_Dragon\"><i>House of the Dragon</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mysaria&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: House of the Dragon\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The television series <i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i> interprets various events that are disputed in the historical record. In the show, Mysaria is from <a href=\"/index.php/Yi_Ti\" title=\"Yi Ti\">Yi Ti</a> instead of <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a>, and a brothel proprietor.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> Mysaria's supposed pregnancy at <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a> is presented as a lie that Daemon made up as part of an attempt to provoke his brother, also writing to the <a href=\"/index.php/Small_council\" title=\"Small council\">small council</a> that he would take her as his second wife in the custom of <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Valyria\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Old Valyria\">Old Valyria</a>. She did not know of this until Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Otto_Hightower\" title=\"Otto Hightower\">Otto Hightower</a> arrived at Dragonstone for the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_egg\" title=\"Dragon egg\">dragon egg</a>, and was deeply upset that Daemon put her life in danger.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rhbohotds01e02.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rhbohotds01e02.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> Mysaria becomes an information broker with a spy network in King's Landing,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rhbohotds01e04.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rhbohotds01e04.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> before an agent of <a href=\"/index.php/Larys_Strong\" title=\"Larys Strong\">Larys Strong</a> burns her manse,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rhbohotds01e09.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rhbohotds01e09.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup> driving her out of the city. She comes to Dragonstone, and while on the island, acts as a go-between with Daemon for the hiring of <a href=\"/index.php/Blood_and_Cheese\" title=\"Blood and Cheese\">Blood and Cheese</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rhbohotds02e01.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rhbohotds02e01.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> then becomes a spy mistress for Rhaenyra as well as a love interest.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rhbohotds02e03.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rhbohotds02e03.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rhbohotds02e06.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rhbohotds02e06.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mysaria&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Blood_(butcher)\" title=\"Blood (butcher)\">He</a> also gave up a description of the <a href=\"/index.php/Whore\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Whore\">whore</a> he claimed had hired <a href=\"/index.php/Blood_and_Cheese\" title=\"Blood and Cheese\">them</a>: an older woman, foreign by her talk, cloaked and hooded, very pale. The other harlots called her Misery.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_a_son_for_a_son.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Let <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon</a> slake his hungers where he will, and we shall do the same.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a>, regarding Mysaria</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mysaria&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: External links\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://gameofthrones.fandom.com/wiki/Mysaria\">Mysaria</a> on the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://gameofthrones.fandom.com/wiki/Wiki_of_Westeros\">Wiki of Westeros</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mysaria&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">In a now deleted blog post, <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a> confirmed that hearing of Maelor's death was what drove Helaena to commit suicide, out of grief and guilt.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mysaria&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-ref